1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,500
Paperwork is hardest when dense language, typing,
or repeated details are a barrier.

2
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:15,000
VocaForm turns an uploaded everyday form into a voice-guided interview
and returns a verified completed document.

3
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:23,000
Here I upload a synthetic medical PDF. GPT-5.6 Sol reads both text and layout,
then compiles the unfamiliar form into a strict, evidence-backed schema:

4
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:32,000
fields, requiredness, dependencies, validation, and exact render targets.
The readiness gate blocks unsupported questions before any interview begins.

5
00:00:32,000 --> 00:00:40,000
There is no manual field mapping.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Now OpenAI Realtime conducts a natural, low-latency conversation.
It is not GPT-5.6 Sol; it is the voice layer.

7
00:00:49,000 --> 00:01:01,000
As I answer, versioned application tools validate and save grounded values atomically,
so a duplicate call or interrupted response cannot silently write twice.

8
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:12,000
If the connection drops, VocaForm rebuilds context from server-owned state
and resumes at the first unresolved question.

9
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Every answer keeps its source and exact spoken wording,
and the keyboard path provides the same core journey.

10
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:35,000
I kept consent, memory, validation, application state, and rendering authoritative in code;
the models cannot silently save memory or change an answer.

11
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:44,000
Review begins with deterministic checks for missing, invalid,
or dependency-sensitive answers.

12
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:53,000
GPT-5.6 Sol then performs a separate non-mutating semantic verification
for contradictions, ambiguity, or unsupported normalization.

13
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:00,000
It can flag an issue, but it cannot edit the form.
Final export is tied to this exact session version.

14
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
VocaForm fills a copied AcroForm PDF, reports one hundred percent placement coverage,
and confirms that the uploaded source was not changed.

15
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:13,000
On a second form, the Memory Vault suggests only three contact facts
I explicitly approved. Nothing is applied until I confirm each value.

16
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:25,000
The medical answers never entered memory, and I can correct or forget a claim
without silently changing an existing form.

17
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:34,000
I used Codex with GPT-5.6 to rebuild the prototype as a modular TypeScript application,
preserve the proven document logic through adapters,

18
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:42,000
and create the accessibility, evaluation, and resilience gates.
Human decisions defined privacy, consent, model roles, and scope.
The live compiler replay found all fifty-three expected fields with zero fabrication.

19
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:50,000
VocaForm: upload, talk, review, download.
One form, one conversation, done—paperwork made human.
